I’ll be what you want me to be.

Charity and love are healing;
These will give the clearest sight;
When I saw my brother&rsquo;s failing,
I was not exactly right.
Now I&rsquo;ll take no further trouble;
Jesus&rsquo; love is all my theme;
Little motes are but a bubble
When I think upon the beam.

Hold to the rod, the iron rod;
&rsquo;Tis strong, and bright, and true.
The iron rod is the word of God;
&rsquo;Twill safely guide us through.

